These Foreign Infusions of Thought and Language (to use the Name which Mr. Addison has given them) are very discernible to any one of a tolerable Taste: 'tis true, they must have some∣thing of a new Air; but they still  a distinct Resemblance of the Old, some∣thing like that of the Sister Neids in Ovid;

