A sort of Comprehension, as I should chuse to call it, for want of some better Name. 'Tis when any Great View is compleat∣ly contracted into a few Lines; but to come up perfectly to my Notion, it should be such a View as is sufficient to fill the whole Mind: We are, in a man∣ner, surrounded with it on all sides; and which ever way we turn our Eyes, we cannot look out of i. This is the Case, where Ulysses is represented in his Ship∣wrack on the Coast of Phoeacia;

Above, sharp Rocks forbid access; around,

