In giving ones Opinion of an exqui∣site Statue we may say, it lives or speaks: but when we go to refine on this, we grow affected and mean. Pardon me if I take this to be the Case in the las Line of this Couplet:

Alive each animated Frame appears;

Od. 7, 123—94. And still to live, beyond the Power of Year

Again:

His arms he stretch'd; his arms the touch deceive;

Od. 11, 487—391. Nor in the fond embrace, embraces give.

Thus is Sisyphus describ'd in the for∣mer Picture;

With many a weary step, and many a groan,

Od 11, 736—594. Up the high hill he heaves a huge round stone.
